# SimpleCalc Bug Fix Walkthrough

## Bug Found

**Left-associative operators (`-`, `/`) were evaluated right-to-left**, giving wrong results:

| Expression | Before (wrong) | After (correct) |
|---|---|---|
| `10 - 5 - 2` | `7.0` | `3.0` |
| `20 / 4 / 5` | `25.0` | `1.0` |

**Root cause**: The while-loop in [evaluateExpression](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/SimpleCalc/src/SimpleCalc.java#73-114) only popped operators with *strictly higher* precedence. It didn't pop same-precedence operators, so `10 - 5 - 2` was evaluated as `10 - (5 - 2)` instead of [(10 - 5) - 2](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/SimpleCalc/src/ArrayStack.java#42-51).

## Fix Applied

#### [MODIFY] [SimpleCalc.java](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/SimpleCalc/src/SimpleCalc.java)

Changed one line — the while-loop condition on line 98:

```diff
-while (!operatorStack.isEmpty() && !hasPrecedence(operatorStack.peek(), tokens.get(i))) {
+while (!operatorStack.isEmpty()
+        && (!hasPrecedence(operatorStack.peek(), tokens.get(i))
+        || hasPrecedence(tokens.get(i), operatorStack.peek()))) {
```

The added condition [hasPrecedence(tokens.get(i), operatorStack.peek())](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/SimpleCalc/src/SimpleCalc.java#149-172) catches same-precedence operators and pops them too, ensuring left-to-right evaluation. [hasPrecedence](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/SimpleCalc/src/SimpleCalc.java#149-172) was **not modified**.

## Test Results — 17/17 passing

```
PASS: 2 + 3 = 5.0
PASS: 10 - 3 = 7.0
PASS: 4 * 5 = 20.0
PASS: 20 / 4 = 5.0
PASS: 10 % 3 = 1.0
PASS: 2 ^ 3 = 8.0
PASS: 10 - 5 - 2 = 3.0
PASS: 20 / 4 / 5 = 1.0
PASS: 2 + 3 - 1 = 4.0
PASS: 2 + 3 * 4 = 14.0
PASS: 10 - 2 * 3 = 4.0
PASS: 2 + 6 / 3 = 4.0
PASS: (2 + 3) * 4 = 20.0
PASS: (10 - 2) * (3 + 1) = 32.0
PASS: ((2 + 3)) = 5.0
PASS: 2 ^ 3 ^ 2 = 64.0
PASS: 3 + 4 * 2 / (1 - 5) ^ 2 = 3.5
```
